1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

2 $q(s_{t},a)$

$s_1$ u $s_2$ Q u: -24r: -13d: -0.29l: +40$\gamma$ 0.9

$$ \begin{align} q(s_{t},a) & = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) \\ & =(-0.1) + (0.9)*(40) \\ & =(35.9) \end{align} $$

import random
import numpy as np

actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    policy = np.ones(len(actions)) * epsilon/len(actions)
    greedy = np.argmax(list(qline.values()))
    policy[greedy] = 1.0 - epsilon + (epsilon/len(actions))
    action = None
    if True: # 
        action =  np.random.choice(actions, p=policy)# 
    else: 
        action = actions[greedy]#  Q 
    return action

In [20]:
epoch = 200
maze_size = (6,6)
trap_number = 1

epsilon0 = 0.5
gamma_list=[0.1, 0.9]
alpha_list=[0.01, 0.5, 0.9]

from Runner import Runner

for alpha in alpha_list:
    for gamma in gamma_list:
        
        g = Maze(maze_size=maze_size,trap_number=trap_number)
        r = Robot(g,alpha=alpha, epsilon0=epsilon0, gamma=gamma)
        r.set_status(learning=True)
        
        print('alpha:{},gamma:{}'.format(alpha, gamma))
        
        runner = Runner(r, g)
        runner.run_training(epoch, display_direction=True)
        runner.plot_results()
        print('\n')
